  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Patatas bravas are chunky fried or roasted potatoes with a sharp, spiced tomato sauce. The sauce is what makes them distinctive: tomatoes, smoked paprika, vinegar, and a little heat, cooked down until thick. The potatoes need to be properly crisp; this recipe achieves it in the oven rather than deep-fat frying."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "What you need" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "defaultServings": 4,
          "items": [
            { "ingredientSlug": "potato", "amount": 800, "unit": "g", "prepNote": "cut into 3 cm chunks, unpeeled", "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the potatoes" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "olive-oil", "amount": 3, "unit": "tbsp", "prepNote": null, "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the potatoes" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine", "amount": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "prepNote": null, "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the potatoes" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "olive-oil", "amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "prepNote": null, "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the sauce" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "garlic", "amount": 2, "unit": "clove", "prepNote": "finely chopped", "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the sauce" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "tomato-puree", "amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "prepNote": null, "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the sauce" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "tinned-tomatoes", "amount": 400, "unit": "g", "prepNote": null, "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the sauce" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "paprika-smoked", "amount": 2, "unit": "tsp", "prepNote": null, "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the sauce" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "cayenne-pepper", "amount": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "prepNote": "or more to taste", "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the sauce" },
            { "ingredientSlug": "sherry-vinegar", "amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "prepNote": null, "isOptional": false, "groupLabel": "For the sauce" }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Method" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Roast the potatoes" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C. Toss the potato chunks with {{olive-oil}} of olive oil and salt. Spread in a single layer on a roasting tray. Roast for 30 to 35 minutes, turning once halfway through, until golden and crisp on the outside."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Make the brava sauce" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat the remaining olive oil in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add {{tomato-puree}} of tomato purée and cook for 1 minute more. Add the tinned tomatoes, {{paprika-smoked}} of smoked paprika, {{cayenne-pepper}} of cayenne, and {{sherry-vinegar}} of sherry vinegar."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Simmer for 15 minutes until thick. Season with salt. Blend briefly for a smoother sauce, or leave slightly chunky."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Serve" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pile the hot roasted potatoes in a bowl or on a flat plate. Spoon the brava sauce generously over the top. Serve immediately."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "The potatoes are not crisp",
              "cause": "Too crowded on the tray, or oven not hot enough",
              "fix": "Use two trays if needed so the potatoes are in a single layer with space between them. Crowding traps steam and prevents crisping."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "The sauce is too sharp",
              "cause": "Too much vinegar or cayenne",
              "fix": "Add a pinch of sugar to balance. Taste before adding all the vinegar."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Where this dish lives" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Patatas bravas are found on tapas menus across Spain and have become one of the most recognisable Spanish foods outside the country. In Madrid they are eaten at bar counters with a cold beer. The sauce varies by region: Catalonia sometimes uses aioli alongside, other regions make a milder sauce. The potatoes themselves are always the constant."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
